narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend ITAL 120 for a fellow student. Italian is a great language to learn. Class difficulty varies greatly among teachers, so do your research! Overall, it is a very relaxed classroom environment. This course can be a lot of work and the tests are not easy...beware! Italian is a great language!
I would absolutely recommend it. Fun, small class size, smart kids, not too much work.
I think Italian 120 is a good continuation to first semester Italian. However, at times I wished I had taken intensive Italian to learn more at a faster rate.
This course is a lot of work, but its really rewarding. As we complete learning the grammar, we discuss culture and the world a lot: this is quite entertaining and a great way to learn.
Absolutely. This class is great and sets you up perfectly positioned to do L3/L4 abroad during the summer or continue your studies the following year.
